Fun Harry Potter themed place! Tried the two main drinks - Mr. Lich's Flaming Brew and Alchemist Concoction. The flaming brew was fun for the visual effects, but it really didn't last long enough. Just long enough for a photo or two and maybe a video. Well, you could keep adding cinnamon until you're satisfied with the effects...but too much cinnamon would probably ruin the drink. The Alchemist Concoction reminded me of a moscow mule. Both drinks were really yummy and I couldn't tell that either of them had alcohol in them. Also tried a chocolate and peanut butter cake (one of the round ones in the display fridge), and it was okay. Not too sweet at least, but not enough peanut butter in my opinion. Kind of like a Reese's peanut butter cup, but not as dense or sweet. It was fun that they also had Harry Potter props for you to dress up in. I thought they could have taken the restaurant one notch further in terms of the theming, but it was not bad (just the reindeer chairs seemed a bit out of place). Overall a fun place to check out if you're a HP fan!  Minus a star since the whole place smelled of truffle oil...I don't remember that in Harry Potter ><

The drinks are the main attraction here, with creatively crafted names and mixture. There's also cocktails served, with one that goes on fire. Personal favorite is the butterscotch ale. Read positive reviews and decided to swing by a Friday evening since we had no plans and were up for adventure.  This review will be lengthy to document an experience that is anything but magical.  1. If the restuarant is full, you are to write down your name and mobile on the waiting list and wait for your turn.  No one told us what to do we just followed what others were doing. 2. During my 1 hour plus wait outside and even at table service, I noticed the 4 - 5 staff were happy just hiding behind the cake counter and chatting amongst themselves. There is plenty you can do on the service floor, like top up our water when they run low or asking if everything was okie (especially when you know your customers have waited for a long time to be seated). 3. After the long wait with our orders placed, we were told many items were sold out. With already a very lean menu, and items off the list it does seem you were unprepared for Friday evening crowds, this is bad supply planning.  It would have been decent to tell your customers in the waiting line if you are expecting to run out of items so they have a choice to continue waiting, head off somewhere else or make a choice on whatever is still available. It's not nice to tell your customers who are tired and hungry from waiting that almost nothing is left on the menu. 4. If this is intended to be themed restaurant, at least make the effort to dress it up like one. Did not look like anything from a Harry Potter book or the movie. A few wooden wands, witches hats and capes does not count as being 'themetic'. 5. Strictly from a non-alcoholic view point - quite a number of items are with alcohol, then maybe you might want to consider expanding your menu to have a wider range to cater for well..non drinkers.  All in all, a huge disappointment. Food was mediocre, service when available was sub-standard and the distance to travel to this place just wasn't worth it. A restaurant business is more than just instagramable, gimicky f&b.

You can pretty much guess where the inspiration for Platform 1094, a wizardry-themed restaurant nestled in the corners of 1094 Serangoon Road. Just try to resist shouting "abracadabra" upon stepping into the magic-inspired cafe! From its decor and ambience to its food and beverages, Platform 1094 exudes magic and wizardry. With rustic chandelier lights fixtures, a long wooden table that takes centerpiece in the restaurant, as well as chairs with mystical prints on it, there are plenty of opportunities to snap that perfect Instagram picture ‚Äì a variety of props, including witches' hats and wands are also provided to make your experience more magical!

This restaurant has alot of interesting meals. The pork ribs and duck dishes were amazing and their desserts were all beautifully plated. Also loved their signature drink as we had alot of fun with it. Worth a visit, especially if you are a potterhead!

Great food at reasonable prices. Service staff were a little overwhelmed though, was quite hard getting their attention when seated in a corner. Decor was a little sparse. Harry potter props were a fun little touch. The flaming brew is a must have for people looking for abit of magic.

Five stars for dessert. Two for everything else. Platform 1094 is a harry potter themed cafe that very carefully walks the line with copyright issues, sadly falling short of being magical. The "Mr. Lich's Flaming Brew" (which is no doubt what you came for) is some kind of blue juice with a flaming floater of Bacardi rum sparked with cinnamon. Super fun to play with, not super tasty. The food and drinks were meh overall (though the truffle fries were quite tasty). We were prepared to leave a bit disappointed, having ticked off a visit to this homage to the wizarding world when the desserts came. Hold on to your witches hat because these are shockingly impressive. The presentation, the flavors, the creativity - these were fine dining New York Michelin Zagat style desserts. We were floored.  My advice: go put your name on the list, get dinner across the street while you wait, then come back for dessert and a flaming brew for photo ops.
have a Magical experience here! .. love this place! ‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§

The theme of the cafe is uniquely one of a kind! The Wizard theme is very refreshing and I dare say it is the only restaurant in Singapore to have such an innovative idea. Next up has to be the food, it is mind-blowingly good! Especially the crab meat pasta and the pork ribs, they are really to die for! Like they say 'Die Die must try la' If you are not a big eater and just want some desserts and drinks, do try the Bloodberry, this is a plated dessert which is good for 2-3 people to share. As for the drinks, there is definitely only 1 choice, the Goblet of Fire, if not for anything, you have to order it for the visual effects and it makes a hell of a great insta picture!
Nice concept.. Quite good service. They are new but trying really hard to give you a good experience..
